as of this disease in a book full of intimate stories--including riveting courtroom testimony, secret investigations of women and doctors for abortion, and startling media portraits of children with disabilities. In exploring a disease that changed America, Dangerous Pregnancies powerfully illuminates social movements that still shape individual lives, pregnancy, medicine, law, and politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAbnormalities, HumanxHistoryxUnited States. 0aAbnormalities, HumanzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aAbortionxHistoryxUnited States. 0aAbortionzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aDisability awarenessxHistoryxUnited States. 0aDisability awarenesszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRubella in pregnancyxHistoryxUnited States. 0aRubella in pregnancyzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRubellaxHistoryxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aRubellazUnited StatesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945005423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520945005.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles